<subSubSection id="C3046550FF87FFD428C315D81D8AFE9B" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="48" pageId="7" pageNumber="47" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA136DBFF87FFDB28C315D818D5F951" blockId="7.[151,1437,1630,2004]" pageId="7" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC9FF87FFDB28C315D81D29F978" bold="true" box="[198,326,1707,1733]" pageId="7" pageNumber="47">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Each elytron only with 
<number id="3DD624FCFF87FFDB2A6815DF1E13F97B" box="[621,636,1708,1734]" pageId="7" pageNumber="47" value="3.0">3</number>
longitudinal costae, costa 
<number id="3DD624FCFF87FFDB2BB815DF1FA4F97B" box="[957,971,1708,1734]" pageId="7" pageNumber="47" value="3.0">3</number>
entirely absent, reticulate cells largely rectangular, regular. Phallus straight, paramerae slightly longer than half of phallus length.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA136DBFF87FFD428C3158B1D8AFE9B" blockId="7.[151,1437,1630,2004]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1436,152,294]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="48" pageId="7" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC9FF87FFDB28C3158B1D13F8AF" bold="true" box="[198,380,1784,1810]" pageId="7" pageNumber="47">Redescription.</emphasis>
Interocular distance 
<number id="3DD624FCFF87FFDB2A8F158A1EC0F8AE" box="[650,687,1785,1811]" pageId="7" pageNumber="47" value="1.4">1.4</number>
times longer than eye diameter. Antennae almost filiform, antennomere 
<number id="3DD624FCFF87FFDB294714531D3DF887" box="[322,338,1824,1850]" pageId="7" pageNumber="47" value="3.0">3</number>
slightly longer than half of 
<number id="3DD624FCFF87FFDB2ABF14531EA6F887" box="[698,713,1824,1850]" pageId="7" pageNumber="47" value="4.0">4</number>
(
<figureCitation id="13252A5EFF87FFDB2AD914531F53F887" box="[732,828,1824,1850]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 19" captionStartId="4.[151,274,1921,1945]" captionTargetBox="[241,1367,718,1920]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[238,1367,668,1944]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 19. Basal antennomeres: (10) Lycomorphon elongaticolle; (11) L. opacum; (12) L. nitidum; (13) L. diversicolle; (14) L. bimaculatum; (15) L. fulvohumaralis; (16) L. amazonicum; (17) L. brasiliense; (18) L. bolivianum; (19) L. irregularis. Scales 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/188407/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="47">
Fig. 
<number id="3DD624FCFF87FFDB2B1C14531F53F887" box="[793,828,1824,1850]" pageId="7" pageNumber="47" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
). Mandibles reduced, almost hooked. Pronotum trapezoidal, dark brown, with simple carina in anterior half and longitudinal groove in posterior half. Anterior thoracic spiracles short, tubular. Elytra elongate, convergent in apical third, dark brown with yellow macula in posterior ¾, separated from sutural costae. Each elytron with 
<number id="3DD624FCFF87FFDB2B8614E71FFDF813" box="[899,914,1940,1966]" pageId="7" pageNumber="47" value="3.0">3</number>
strong longitudinal costae, costa 
<number id="3DD624FCFF87FFDB2D2C14E71957F813" box="[1321,1336,1940,1966]" pageId="7" pageNumber="47" value="3.0">3</number>
entirely absent, costa 
<number id="3DD624FCFF87FFDB293A14C91D21F869" box="[319,334,1978,2004]" pageId="7" pageNumber="47" value="1.0">1</number>
missing apically, reticulate cells regular, largely rectangular. Abdominal sternum 
<number id="3DD624FCFF87FFDB2D4B14C91932F869" box="[1358,1373,1978,2004]" pageId="7" pageNumber="47" value="8.0">8</number>
with rounded emargination distally. Sternum 
<number id="3DD624FCFF88FFD42A7D13EB1EE8FF0F" box="[632,647,152,178]" pageId="8" pageNumber="48" value="9.0">9</number>
elongate, rounded proximally, triangular distally (
<figureCitation id="13252A5EFF88FFD42CE613EB1942FF0F" box="[1251,1325,152,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="3.[151,270,1595,1619]" captionTargetBox="[216,1386,192,1594]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[196,1392,151,1596]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. (1 – 3) Pronotum in dorsal view: (1) Lycomorphon diversicolle; (2) L. opacum; (3) L. brasiliense. (4 – 6) Abdominal sternum 8: (4) L. bimaculatum; (5) L. bolivianum; (6) L. irregularis. (7 – 8) Terminal abdominal segments in ventral view: (7) L. nitidum; (8) L. opacum. (9) elytron of L. opacum. Scales 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/188406/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number id="3DD624FCFF88FFD42D1913EB1942FF0F" box="[1308,1325,152,178]" pageId="8" pageNumber="48" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
). Phallus straight, teary orifice in distal half of phallus. Paramerae slightly longer than half of phallus length, rounded apically in lateral and ventral views. Phallobase almost transversal (
<figureCitation id="13252A5EFF88FFD42BB813961820FF42" box="[957,1103,229,255]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 37" captionStartId="5.[151,272,1919,1943]" captionTargetBox="[259,1316,214,1871]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[243,1345,197,1892]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 37. Male genitalia: (20 – 22) Lycomorphon elongaticolle; (23 – 25) L. angusticolle; (26 – 28) L. opacum; (29 – 31) L. nitidum; (32 – 34) L. diversicolle; (35 – 37) L. bimaculatum. (20, 23, 26, 29, 32, 35) ventral view; (21, 24, 27, 30, 33, 36) dorsal view; (22, 25, 28, 31, 34, 37) lateral view. Scales 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/188408/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="48">
Figs. 
<number id="3DD624FCFF88FFD42C0413961820FF42" box="[1025,1103,229,255]" pageId="8" pageNumber="48" value="30.0" valueMax="31.0" valueMin="29.0">29–31</number>
</figureCitation>
). Body length: 
<quantity id="4CE69B3EFF88FFD42D03139619F7FF42" box="[1286,1432,229,255]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.85" metricValueMax="6.2" metricValueMin="5.5" pageId="8" pageNumber="48" unit="mm" value="5.85" valueMax="6.2" valueMin="5.5">5.5–6.2 mm</quantity>
, humeral width: 
<quantity id="4CE69B3EFF88FFD42955127F1D8EFE9B" box="[336,481,268,294]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2999999999999998" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="8" pageNumber="48" unit="mm" value="1.2999999999999998" valueMax="1.4" valueMin="1.2">1.2–1.4 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
